[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":327},["ShallowReactive",2],{"github-repo-octo-kumo/desktop-widgets":3,"z6fUHfxkMg":4,"github-repo-api-octo-kumo/desktop-widgets-rls":162,"github-repo-api-octo-kumo/desktop-widgets":254},"# Timetable Widget\n\n# How to use\n\n![img.png](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/octo-kumo/desktop-widgets/master/images/img.png)\n![img.png](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/octo-kumo/desktop-widgets/master/images/img2.png)\n1. Upon launch no window is displayed, you should see a tray icon appearing.\n2. You might also be asked for minerva credentials, you can cancel if you want to key them in later.\n3. Right-click on the tray icon to access settings.\n\n## Timetable\n\n- Crawls timetable from `Minerva > Student Menu > Registration Menu > View Weekly Class Schedule`\n- Displays the timetable for today on your bottom right.\n\n## Auto Login\n\n- If you do not use auto login, your credentials are not stored, but you have to key them in everytime you try to\n  refresh.\n- If you do use auto login, they are only stored in your computer under whatever place java preferences are.\n\n## Make it run on startup\n\n1. Download the latest release from here\n2. Put it somewhere safe\n3. Press `Win + R` to open up run\n4. Type `shell:startup` and press enter to bring up startup folder\n5. Create a shortcut to the jar file and move it here\n",{"data":5,"body":8,"excerpt":-1,"toc":156},{"title":6,"description":7},"Timetable Widget","",{"type":9,"children":10},"root",[11,19,25,39,59,66,87,93,106,112],{"type":12,"tag":13,"props":14,"children":16},"element","h1",{"id":15},"timetable-widget",[17],{"type":18,"value":6},"text",{"type":12,"tag":13,"props":20,"children":22},{"id":21},"how-to-use",[23],{"type":18,"value":24},"How to use",{"type":12,"tag":26,"props":27,"children":28},"p",{},[29,35],{"type":12,"tag":30,"props":31,"children":34},"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"img.png","https://raw.githubusercontent.com/octo-kumo/desktop-widgets/master/images/img.png",[],{"type":12,